Branching Statement:
Branching statement is used to transfer the control from one statement to another statement
according to the condition of program.
Three types of branching statement:
1)break(use only loop and switch)
2)continue(use only loop)
3)goto
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1)break:
break statement can be used with switch and in the block of any loop.
break keyword stops the iteration of loop and transfer control out of loop.

Syntax:
break;
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
continue:
continue statement is also used in the block of loop.When continue statement is executed then 
it stops the current iteration and continue loop from next iteration.

Syntax:
continue;

Example:
for(i=1;i<=5;i++)
{
   printf("Befor the continue statement !");//executed all the times means 5 times
   if(i>=3)
      continue;
   printf("After the continue statement !");//executed 2 times for 1 and 2	  
} 
Example 2:


#include<stdio.h>
#include<conio.h>
void main()
{
  int num,i,p=0;
  clrscr();
  printf("Enter any five values:")
  for(i=1;i<=5;i++)
  {
     scanf("%d",&num);
	 if(num<0)
	   continue;
	 p=p+1;  
  }
   printf("Total positive values=%d",p);
   getch();
}

output:
Enter any five values:-20 1 20 -45 0
Total positive values=3

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
goto statement:
goto statement is a keyword that is used to transfer the control one statement to
another statement of the program.
 Where the control will transfer itis defined by label defined with goto.
 
 Syntax:
 
 label:
 
 //statement;
 
 goto label;
 
 
 Example:
 #include<stdio.h>
 #include<conio.h>
 void main()
 {
    int amt,op,wamt,camt;
	char opt;
	clrscr();
	printf("Enter total amount in your bank:");
	scanf("%d",&amt);
	start:
	printf("Enter 1 for withdraw and 2 for credit:");
	scanf("%d",&op);
	if(op==1)
	{
	   printf("Enter your withdrawal Amout:");
	   scanf("%d",&wamt);
	   amt=amt-wamt;
	   printf("After Withdrawl Your Avilable Balance = %d",amt);
	}
	else if(op==2)
	{
	   printf("Enter your Credit Amount:");
	   scanf("%d",&camt);
	   amt=amt+camt;
	   printf("After credit your Total Balance = %d",amt);
	}
	else{
	   printf("Please Enter A Vailid Option 1 or 2 !");
	}
	
	fflush(stdin);
	printf("Enter y for continue and n for exit:");
	scanf("%c",&opt);
	if(opt=='y')
	  goto start;
	else if(opt=='n')
     	goto end;
    end:
    getch();
 }
